Mol Confirms Release of Second Kidnapped Pakistani Contractor

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n   a n d   A n w a r   S h a k i r
-- 
2011-07-14T12:14:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/mol-confirms-release-of-second-kidnapped-pakistani-contractor.html
Mol Nyrt.,  Hungary ’s largest oil
refiner, confirmed that both the people kidnapped while working
for a supplier to the company’s Pakistani unit have been
released by captors.  Mol spokesman Johannes Vetter confirmed the second worker’s
release in an e-mailed statement today.  Suspected Islamic militants kidnapped an engineer and his
driver after attacking a convoy returning from a drilling site
west of Kohat town in northwest  Pakistan  on Jan. 20. Two workers
and four paramilitary police personnel were killed in the
attack.  Mol confirmed yesterday the release of one of the two
people kidnapped.  To contact the reporter on this story:
